{"type":"message","id":"bc894151","parentId":"5deb8676","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:58:16.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron run is blocked by the exec security policy. The error says \"Cron runs cannot wait for interactive exec approval\" - this means the cron is running without a TTY and can't get approval.\n\nLooking at the policy settings, the issue is:\n- security=allowlist\n- ask=on-miss \n- askFallback=deny\n\nThe cron runs cannot interactively approve, so it needs either:\n1. security=\"full\" and ask=\"off\" - for trusted local automation\n2. Add an explicit allowlist entry for this command\n3. Enable Web UI, terminal UI, or chat exec approvals and rerun interactively\n\nSince this is a weather cache refresh that should run automatically, the best fix is to add an allowlist entry. But wait - I'm in the cron context and can't modify the approvals file. The user needs to do this.\n\nActually, let me look at the exec-approvals.json path mentioned - I could potentially add an entry there if I knew what the structure looks like. But actually the better approach is: the cron job payload should be configured differently.\n\nLet me check the cron job to see how it's configured:\n","thinkingSignature":"d13bdd1fd66f0e2088a990c9e7712a16a4329e37a7b9bbf3d83801315117e35e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe cron job execution is being blocked by the exec security policy. The issue is that \"cron runs cannot wait for interactive exec approval\" - meaning there's no TTY available for user approval during cron execution.\n\nThe fix requires either:\n1. Adding this command to the allowlist, or\n2. Setting `security=\"full\"` and `ask=\"off\"` for trusted local automation\n\nWould you like me to add an allowlist entry for this weather API curl command, or would you prefer to adjust the exec policy? I can show you the current allowlist configuration.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xibvms9b7a5l_1","name":"read","argumen