{"type":"message","id":"ebd3c822","parentId":"1ed82864","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:58:53.293Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a deep issue. The cron job runs in an isolated session, but there are security layers:1. The \"rules\" in exec-approvals.json aren't being applied (perhaps incorrectly formatted or not loaded)\n2. The gateway config paths `tools.exec.security` and `tools.exec.ask` aren't valid for JSON patch\n\nThe user just wants this cron job to run. Let me check the cron format - they included the shell command in the user message so this cronjob will actually trigger again. \n\nWait, looking at the original cron message - it's actually a cron job definition that runs the curl command. The problem is that cron runs can't wait for interactive approval.\n\nThe best approach is to just let them know the cron can't run and suggest a fix. The user's exec-approvals.json isn't working perhaps because rules format. Let me try a simpler approach - check if curl is a safe binary in the first place.\n","thinkingSignature":"86de969a8c0b9b11eaae8012c87ea704d9496e3575970706f25fa6a266c9f277"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4hrnu6pvoi5q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which curl"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":213,"output":214,"cacheRead":46464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46891,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775095129872,"responseId":"061d005aa871a9e24fb62c5ec0e6b899"}}
{"type":"message","id":"962b4d4a","parentId":"ebd3c822","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:58:53.338Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4hrnu6pvoi5q_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"exec\",\n  \"error\": \"exec denied: Cron runs cannot wait for interactive exec approval.\\nEffective host exec policy: security=allowlist ask=on-miss askFallback=deny\\nStricter values from tools.exec and ~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json both apply.\\nFix one of these:\\n- align both files to security=\\\"full\\\" and ask=\\\"off\\\" for trusted local automation\\n- keep allowlist mode and add an explicit allowlist entry for this command\\n- enable Web UI, terminal UI, or chat exec approvals and rerun interactively\\nTip: run \\\"openclaw doctor\\\" and \\\"openclaw approvals get --gateway\\\" to inspect the effective policy.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"exec","error":"exec denied: Cron runs cannot wait for interactive exec approval.\nEffective host exec policy: security=allowlist ask=on-miss askFallback=deny\nStricter values from tools.exec and ~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json both apply.\nFix one of these:\n- align both files to security=\"full\" and ask=\"off\" for trusted local automation\n- keep allowlist mode and add an explicit allowlist entry for this command\n- enable Web UI, terminal UI, or chat exec approvals and rerun interactively\nTip: run \"openclaw doctor\" and \"openclaw approvals get --gateway\" to inspect the effective policy."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775095133336}}
{"type":"message","id":"3824fba8","parentId":"962b4d4a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T01:58:57.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I've been trying multiple approaches to fix this cron execution issue. The gateway config doesn't recognize security/ask as top-level keys in tools.exec. Let me check the exec-approvals.json allowlist entry I created earlier - I think the issue is that the regex pattern might not be matching correctly since the cron runs have specific format or escaping issues.\n\nLooking at the error message more carefully:\n- \"Effective host exec policy: security=allowlist ask=on-miss askFallback=deny\"\n- \"Stricter values from tools.exec and ~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json both apply\"\n\nThe exec-approvals.json has default ask: false but the gateway tools.exec security=allowlist is applying a stricter policy that requires approval.\n\nWait - I think the issue is that the cron job is configured to run on gateway (host mode), but I've been trying to add the allowlist for the localhost exec context. The cron is probably trying to run on the 'host' target which uses a different security policy.\n\nLooking at the error - it says \"Stricter values from tools.exec and ~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json both apply\" which suggests the gateway's security policy is different from what's in exec-approvals.json.\n\nLet me check what exec policy the gateway is using by looking at the full config response I already got. I need to find tools.exec in there.\n","thinkingSignature":"187cce1aff6fbea8f6d4a1c8f5d7b9dbf6e6a36225c2f2a70d90a9f9e592532e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y9w5f5t1xkvr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | jq '.tools.exec'","host":"gateway"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":199,"output":327,"cacheRead":46672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47198,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total